      "writtenOn": "2017-08-28T13:16:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u0027Decode\u0027 and \u0027Encode\u0027 would be enough IMO. \n\nIs there a reason not: \n\nDecode([]byte)(interface{}, error) \nReduce(interface{}, interface{}) (interface{}, error) \nEncode(interface{}) ([]byte, error) \n\nwhere it is assumed that that all instances of \u0027interface{}\u0027 have the same underlying (application dependent type). \nIt\u0027s a bit more typesafe. It has the advantage that a programming error is easier caught if the wrong types are passed around.",
      "revId": "94c49d072af613c3093775cc89052e89a57fb782",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "125eedc8_aa065bc0",
        "filename": "go/gcs/mass_process/reduce.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 21,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-28T13:35:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The problem is that we need to know how to (de)serialize the intermediate type so that we can store and retrieve from GS.  It would have to be something like:\n\ntype Serializable interface {\n    Serialize() ([]byte, error)\n    Deserialize([]byte) error\n}\n\ntype Reduction interface {\n    Decode([]byte) (Serializable, error)\n    Reduce(Serializable, Serializable) (Serializable, error)\n    Encode(Serializable) ([]byte, error)\n}\n\nOr to be even more explicit:\n\ntype Serializable interface {\n    Serialize() ([]byte, error)\n}\ntype Deserializable interface {\n    Deserialize([]byte) error\n}\n\ntype StartRepresentation interface {\n    Deserializable\n}\ntype IntermediateRepresentation interface {\n    Serializable\n    Deserializable\n}\ntype FinalRepresentation interface {\n    Serializable\n}\n\ntype Reduction interface {\n    Decode(StartRepresentation) (IntermediateRepresentation, error)\n    Reduce(IntermediateRepresentation, IntermediateRepresentation) (IntermediateRepresentation, error)\n    Encode(IntermediateRepresentation) (FinalRepresentation, error)\n}",
      "parentUuid": "d598e1a4_7d2a5726",
      "revId": "94c49d072af613c3093775cc89052e89a57fb782",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
